# Next.js 16 App Router

Project uses Next.js 16 (App Router) on Node.js runtime, Turbopack as the default bundler.

## Async Request APIs (BREAKING in v16)

`params`, `searchParams`, `cookies()`, `headers()`, and `draftMode()` are all async. Always `await` them.

```ts
// ❌ BAD (Next 15 style)
export default function Page({ params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
  return <div>{params.id}</div>;
}

// ✅ GOOD
export default async function Page({ params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }) {
  const { id } = await params;
  return <div>{id}</div>;
}
```

In Client Components, unwrap with `use()`:

```tsx
"use client";
import { use } from "react";

export default function Page({ params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }) {
  const { id } = use(params);
  return <div>{id}</div>;
}
```

## Server Components by Default

- Components are server-rendered unless `"use client"` is at the top.
- Add `"use client"` only when state, effects, refs, browser APIs, or event handlers are needed.
- Fetch data in server components close to where it is used; avoid prop-drilling.
- Wrap independently-loading sections with `<Suspense>` and run independent fetches with `Promise.all`.

## Caching (Cache Components Model)

- Caching is **opt-in** in v16. Dynamic code executes at request time by default.
- Mark cacheable work explicitly with `"use cache"`.
- Use `revalidateTag()` for time-based revalidation and `updateTag()` for on-demand updates.

```ts
async function getEntries() {
  "use cache";
  return prisma.weddingGuestbookEntry.findMany();
}
```

## Proxy (formerly Middleware)

- `middleware.ts` is now `proxy.ts`, runs on Node.js by default.
- Use `ProxyRequest` / `ProxyResponse` instead of `NextRequest` / `NextResponse`.
- Define `matcher` config; route matching is no longer implicit.

## Routing & Files

- Keep `src/app/**/page.tsx` and `layout.tsx` thin; compose feature components.
- Place route handlers under `src/app/api/<route>/route.ts`. Prefer delegating logic to `@darchive/api`.
- Use `next/link` for internal navigation and `next/image` for meaningful images.
- Do NOT colocate reusable components under `src/app`. Use `src/features/*` or `src/shared/ui`.

## Build & Tooling

- Turbopack is default for `next dev` and `next build`. Do not add custom webpack config.
- `next lint` is removed; run ESLint directly via `pnpm lint`.
- Node 20.9+, TypeScript 5.1+ required.
